list.comment: Encapsulated the createAirline(String) method in appropriate AirportFactory class

task.summary: Default task
Removed code smells, cleanup.
Added an abstraction for future Transportation facilities (TrainStation, Airport, BoatPort)
Made Airport constructor public so that it can be created with an AirportFactory. Moved createAirport() method to appropriate AirportFactory class.
Removed duplicate code, let the parent have the name of the Airport.
Refactored createAirport(String) method to cooperate with the interface.
Added a method signature, createTransport(String), to create an abstract Transport object.
Renamed file to a "higher level abstraction", so to speak, since Part 2 will require that Boats and Trains have competing companies as well.
Encapsulated the createAirline(String) method in appropriate AirportFactory class
Added createCompany(String) method signature.
Renamed method createAirline(String) to createCompany(String), as required by the interface we are implementing.
Made Company abstract.
Extend the super class.
Added logic to createAirport(String) and createAirline(String) by interacting with the (AirportFactory) TransportationFactory reference.
Created SeatClass enum.
Created abstract Section class. Will have FlightSection, maybe a TrainSection, maybe a BoatSection, etc.
Update the method signature and call super's constructor.
Updated modifiers of methods to public as necessary.
We may need to instantiate a Company in the future, so removing the "abstract" keyword for now.
Encapsulated the createSection(String, String, int, int, String) method to AirportFactory.
Added createSection(String, String, int, int, String) method signature.
Started to build the SampleClient to check for errors as we go.
Created abstract Path class to represent the different travel trips (a flight trip, a boat trip, or a train trip).
Moved attributes to parent class and make a call to super's constructor.
Added remaining method signatures for abstract factory interface.
Implemented methods as required by the TransportationFactory interface.
Updated the logic of SystemManager method's to interact with the airportFactory.
Made Company abstract again. We actually will not instantiate Company itself, but its children polymorphically.

Version 2 of the TransportationFactory interface. The Factory should be responsible for building -- let the SystemManager be responsible for searching for available seats and displaying system information.
Implementing version 2 of the TransportationFactory interface.
Refactored reference of the TransportationFactory.
Deprecated the old TransportationFactory interface.
Added some get methods
Added psuedo-code for findAvailableFlights(...)
Added get method for the ArrayList of Path objects.
rm whitespace
Added logic for findAvailableFlights(...)
Overrode toString() method.
Added get() methods.
Just implement TransportationFactory.
Updated findAvailableFlights(...) method.
TransportationFactory interface is back in da booth.
Updated SampleClient
